//  APPENDIX G
//  A community "clearance" letter (translated, in the source, from
//  Gujarati), referenced in Chapter Eleven. Source: a single handwritten
//  Urdu page, p. 188 of the original edition. Square brackets and italic
//  notes flag readings that are uncertain in the manuscript.
// =====================================================================

#set par(first-line-indent: 0pt, justify: false, leading: 0.75em)

#align(center)[
  #text(size: 10.5pt, style: "italic", fill: luma(70))[(see Chapter Eleven)]
  #v(0.6em)
  #text(size: 14pt, weight: "bold")[Clearance Letter]
  #v(0.15em)
  #text(size: 10pt, style: "italic", fill: luma(70))[(translated from Gujarati)]
]
#v(1em)

// ---- Letterhead -----------------------------------------------------
#align(center)[
  #text(size: 12.5pt, weight: "bold")[Anjuman-e-Hameedi]
  #v(0.25em)
  #set text(size: 9.5pt)
  Santacruz Bohra Jamaat, Station Road \
  Santacruz (West) #h(0.3em) — #h(0.3em) 400 0\[?\]5
]
#v(1.1em)

// ---- Body of the letter ---------------------------------------------
#set par(first-line-indent: 0pt, justify: true, leading: 0.74em)

To the esteemed Fakhr al-Mulk, Sayyidi Saifuddin Sahib,
S.D.T.S.P.E.X.M. #emph[\[a string of honorific abbreviations, as in the
original\]]:

#v(0.4em)

After the loftiest respects and abundant salutations, it is submitted
that the money for the #emph[sabeel] and other dues has been received
from the brother named below. The account of the said brother is
therefore clear, with nothing outstanding, on the books of the Santacruz
Jamaat. A marriage (#emph[nikah]) is to take place at the home of the
said brother, and the Anjuman (the Jamaat Committee) has no objection to
it. This is respectfully submitted.

#v(1em)

// ---- Particulars ----------------------------------------------------
#set par(first-line-indent: 0pt, justify: false, leading: 0.85em)
#pad(left: 0.4em)[
  #grid(
    columns: (auto, 1fr),
    column-gutter: 0.7em,
    row-gutter: 0.55em,
    [*Name:*],         [Hatim Bhai Akbar Ali #emph[\[the word "Manzil" follows here; possibly part of a building name\]]],
    [*Address:*],      [Prem \[Mithyovar?\] Darshan, Hasanabad, Second Lane, Santacruz.],
    [*Bride's name:*], [Hajira Bai Hatim Ali],
  )
]

#v(1.4em)

// ---- Signature ------------------------------------------------------
#align(center)[
  Servant of the Syedna (#emph[Abd-e-Syedna]) \
  T. R. \[Nepterwala?\] \
  #text(style: "italic", fill: luma(70))[(signature)]
]

